article.headline: North Texas 94, Jarvis Christian 70
article.story: DENTON, Texas (AP) -- Calvin Watson scored 27 points and grabbed seven rebounds to help North Texas to a 94-70 win over Jarvis Christian on Friday. Quincy Williams added 15 points and five rebounds for North Texas. Rich Young finished with 11 points and seven rebounds and Ben Bell and Michael Sturns each scored 10. Neville Storer led Jarvis Christian (8-4) with 22 points. Demarion Crite scored 15 and James Woodson had 10. Five North Texas players finished with at least two steals. The Mean Green (9-3) forced 18 turnovers, outscoring Jarvis Christian 29-6 on points off turnovers and 16-2 on fast break points. North Texas blocked seven shots, tying a season high. The Mean Green shot 54 percent from the field. Jarvis Christian shot 36 percent.
